# Chrononaut Development Rules

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 15 App Router, TypeScript strict, shadcn/ui
- Supabase for all backend (auth, database, storage)
- Vercel AI SDK for Claude + Gemini

## Patterns
- Server Components by default
- Client Components only for interactivity (forms, buttons, state)
- Streaming for all AI responses
- All database queries through Supabase client

## AI Agents (4 total)
- Pattern Analyst (Claude Sonnet): background analysis, metrics dashboards
- Executive Coach (Claude Sonnet): writing, meeting preparation, interactive coaching, journal pattern analysis and insights
- Research Assistant (Gemini Flash and Deep Research Mode): speed tasks, web search, market research
- Communications Coach (Gemini Flash): live voice mode only

## Database
- All tables have RLS policies (users own their data)
- Encrypted fields: journal content, meeting transcripts, ai-executive coach feedback
- Unencrypted journal data (queryable): dates, mood labels, scores, metadata

## Code Style
- Descriptive variable names
- Comments for non-obvious logic
- Error handling with user-friendly messages